The paper deals with signal recovery using a weighted $\ell_2/\ell_1$ minimization approach, which is a common technique in the field of information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The focus is on recovering block sparse signals, which is a topic of interest in machine learning (cs.LG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also discusses the use of prior support information, which is relevant to the field of signal processing (cs.SP) and statistical inference (cs.SI).
